<DialogueTree>
    <NameField>Rover</NameField>

    <DialogueNode>
        <Name>Start</Name>
        <EntryCondition>DEFAULT</EntryCondition>
        <Dialogue>
            <Page>TRAPPIST-1c is the second planet around the star TRAPPIST-1.</Page>
        </Dialogue>
        <DialogueOptionsList>
            <DialogueOption>
                <Text>Overview</Text>
                <DialogueTarget>Overview</DialogueTarget>
            </DialogueOption>
            <DialogueOption>
                <Text>Atmosphere</Text>
                <DialogueTarget>Atmosphere</DialogueTarget>
            </DialogueOption>
            <DialogueOption>
                <Text>[Exit]</Text>
                <DialogueTarget>Exit</DialogueTarget>
            </DialogueOption>
        </DialogueOptionsList>
    </DialogueNode>

    <DialogueNode>
        <Name>Overview</Name>
        <Dialogue>
            <Page>TRAPPIST-1c is a terrestrial planet, slightly larger and more massive than Earth, the most massive planet in the TRAPPIST-1 system.</Page>
            <Page>Because of its density, it's likely covered in a thick, Venus-like atmosphere.</Page>
            <Page>It's also probably one of only two planets in the system that isn't completely covered in water.</Page>
        </Dialogue>
        <DialogueOptionsList>
            <DialogueOption>
                <Text>Back</Text>
                <DialogueTarget>Start</DialogueTarget>
            </DialogueOption>
        </DialogueOptionsList>
    </DialogueNode>

    <DialogueNode>
        <Name>Atmosphere</Name>
        <Dialogue>
            <Page>Due to its featureless absorption spectra and moderate density, it's likely covered in a thick, Venus-like atmosphere.</Page>
            <Page>Its atmosphere is likely thinner than that of planet b, and made of either carbon dioxide or water vapor.</Page>
        </Dialogue>
        <DialogueOptionsList>
            <DialogueOption>
                <Text>Back</Text>
                <DialogueTarget>Start</DialogueTarget>
            </DialogueOption>
        </DialogueOptionsList>
    </DialogueNode>

    <DialogueNode>
        <Name>Exit</Name>
        <Dialogue>
            <Page>...</Page>
        </Dialogue>
    </DialogueNode>

</DialogueTree>